    fix(0.7.2): PR-7 FIX-3 — fixed-width RFC3339 fields (codex pass-3 BLOCK)
    
    Codex pass-3 confirmed FIX-2's value-range checks but BLOCKed: the parser
    still accepted non-canonical field widths (2026-6-1T7:3:9Z, +5:00 offset,
    5-digit year) — not truly "strict RFC3339". Added a `fixed_digits(field,
    width)` helper enforcing exact-width, digits-only fields for year(4) /
    month(2) / day(2) / hour(2) / minute(2) / second(2) / offset-hour(2) /
    offset-minute(2). Added 4 width-violation reject cases.
    
    Bin unit 5/5, integration 12/12, clippy clean, committed store exit 0.
    
    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>

