**Findings**
No findings.

`fixed_digits` now enforces exact ASCII-digit widths, and the parser uses it for every fixed-width component the pass-3 BLOCK called out: year/month/day, hour/minute/second, and offset hour/minute ([perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:123), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:149), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:179), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:204)). The unit rejection set explicitly covers the previously accepted non-canonical forms `2026-6-1T7:3:9Z`, `+5:00`, and a 5-digit year in `rfc3339_rejects_malformed` ([perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:543), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:557)).

Canonical behavior remains covered: valid edge cases in `rfc3339_accepts_valid_edge_cases`, UTC normalization in `rfc3339_offset_normalizes_to_utc`, and chronology ordering for the batch-collapse arc in `rfc3339_orders_the_batch_collapse_arc` ([perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:513), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:521), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:530)). I do not see a remaining lenient path that would let a malformed timestamp silently participate in latest-run selection: every row is forced through `parse_rfc3339_epoch` at load time, malformed timestamps become exit-2 errors, and ordering uses parsed `ts_epoch` rather than raw string comparison ([perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:223), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:237), [perf-regression-check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/src/bin/perf-regression-check.rs:391)). The bin-level malformed timestamp path is also exercised ([perf_regression_check.rs](/tmp/fdb-PR-7-20260601T215338Z/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-cli/tests/perf_regression_check.rs:121)).

